oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The steamboat "Gordon C. Greene" band playing at Paris Landing State Park during the Tennessee Valley "HO!" cruise barbecue; Captain Tom Greene is at the piano.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The horn player is Howe Spencer; the drummer is Jimmy Valario; the accordian player is Bobby Roller. Captain Tom Greene died twenty days after this photograph was taken in 1950.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Steamboats; Bands; State parks & reserves; Barbecues; Tourism; Musicians; Lakes & ponds
